
---


@startuml
' Define package if needed
package "Energy Building Portal System" {
  
  ' Actors
  [User] as user
  [Administrator] as admin
  [Visitor] as visitor
  
  ' Use Cases
  [Register User] as uc1
  [Login] as uc2
  [Create Building] as uc3
  [Add Entry to Building] as uc4
  [Comment on Building] as uc5
  [Search Buildings] as uc6
  [Release Entry Publicly] as uc7
  [Delete Comment] as uc8
  [Manage User Accounts] as uc9
  [View Public Building Info] as uc10

  ' Associations between actors and use cases
  user --> uc1
  user --> uc2
  user --> uc3
  user --> uc4
  user --> uc5
  user --> uc7
  visitor --> uc6
  visitor --> uc10
  admin --> uc2
  admin --> uc8
  admin --> uc9

  ' Generalization: Administrator is-a User
  user <|-- admin

  ' Classes
  class WebPortal {
    - version: String
    - url: String
    + getBuildings(): List<Building>
  }

  class User {
    - username: String
    - email: String
    - password: String
    - activated: Boolean
    + register(): void
    + login(): Boolean
  }

  class Administrator {
    - idCardNumber: String
    + deleteUser(user: User): void
    + deleteComment(comment: Comment): void
  }

  class Building {
    - id: String
    - name: String
    - energyClass: Char (A/B/C/D)
    - address: String
    - yearOfConstruction: Integer
    - owner: User
    - profileImage: Image
    + addEntry(entry: Entry): void
    + addComment(comment: Comment): void
  }

  class Entry {
    - name: String
    - public: Boolean
    * type-specific subclasses below
  }

  class TextualEntry {
    - content: String
  }

  class NumericalEntry {
    - value: Double
    - unit: String
  }

  class Image {
    - fileName: String
  }

  class Comment {
    - content: String
    - author: User
    - building: Building
  }

  class FullTextSearch {
    - query: String
    + search(query: String): List<Building>
  }

  ' Inheritance for Entry types
  Entry <|-- TextualEntry
  Entry <|-- NumericalEntry

  ' Relationships
  User "1" -- "0..*" Building : owns
  Building "1" -- "0..*" Entry : contains
  Building "1" -- "0..*" Comment : has
  User "1" -- "0..*" Comment : author
  WebPortal "1" -- "0..*" User : users
  WebPortal "1" -- "0..*" Building : buildings
  WebPortal "1" -- "1" FullTextSearch : provides
  Building "1" -- "1" Image : profilePhoto
}

@enduml

---

### 🧩 Explanation of Key Elements:

#### **Actors & Use Cases**
- **User**: Registers, logs in, creates buildings, adds entries/comments.
- **Visitor**: Can search and view public building info.
- **Administrator**: Manages users and deletes comments.

#### **Generalization**
- `Administrator` inherits from `User`.

#### **Classes and Relationships**
- `Entry` is abstract with two concrete types: `TextualEntry` and `NumericalEntry`.
- A `Building` has an `owner`, multiple `Entry`s, and a `profileImage`.
- `FullTextSearch` supports searching across all `Building`s via any actor.

